HEADWORD: Orvietan
<hw>Or`vi*e"tan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>orvi⟦eacute⟧tan</ets>: cf. It. <ets>orvietano</ets>. So called
because invented at <etsep>Orvieto</etsep>, in Italy.]</ety> <def>A kind
of antidote for poisons; a counter poison formerly in vogue.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
